@startuml activity-log-segmentation
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because this view is a decision-centric control flow with a three-clause branch
'' guard and a coloured pushdown note — an activity diagram expresses the regular-classify / context-free-depth
'' interplay and the loop-until-batch-drained cadence far more precisely than a Mermaid flowchart. Step colours:
'' teal (RENDERER_FILL/RENDERER_TINT) = renderer parser steps; amber (IPC_TINT, and the note) = the WPDA
'' pushdown, which lives on the IPC/seam palette.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Log segmentation — the per-line boundary decision (regular classify + context-free depth)

start
repeat
  :read the next line L from the batch;
  :classify L (REGULAR):\ncontinuation?(L) via the continuation regex; <<RENDERER_FILL>>
  :read brace depth = depth(F)\n**before** applying L's braces; <<RENDERER_FILL>>
  if (depth = 0  and  not continuation(L)  and  a record is open?) then (boundary: new record)
    :emit the open record\n(one :record IR block, stable anchor-id); <<RENDERER_TINT>>
    :start a fresh open record with L;
  else (same record)
    :append L to the open record;
  endif
  :advance the pushdown by net-brace(L)\n(|net-brace| ob/cb tokens through advance-step); <<IPC_TINT>>
  note right #FFF6D6: the brace STACK is what keeps a multi-line\nJSON entry ONE record — a header-looking\nline at depth > 0 can never trigger a boundary
repeat while (more lines in this batch?) is (yes) not (no / batch drained)
:on finish, flush the still-open record;
stop

@enduml
